Key Match Events: Emmanuel Clase, MLB's best closer, imploded in the eighth inning.
Jhonkensy Noel hit a game-tying, two-out, two-run home run in the ninth inning.
David Fry hit a two-out, two-run, walk-off home run in the 10th inning.
Aaron Judge and Giancarlo Stanton hit back-to-back tying and go-ahead home runs off Clase.
Andrés Giménez made a crucial defensive play in the top of the 10th inning to retire Jazz Chisholm Jr.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Stephen Vogt emphasized the team's resilience, stating, 'We never quit. We get punched in the teeth pretty hard there in the eighth, and our guys stepped up huge for the guy [Clase] that carried us all year long.'
Jhonkensy Noel commented on the team's focus, saying, 'The goal is to get to the World Series. When we get to that point, that’s when we’re going to be a little more celebratory mode.'
David Fry reflected on the unexpected turn of events, noting, 'We got punched in the mouth with the best pitcher in baseball, Emmanuel Clase.'
Manager Stephen Vogt praised Andrés Giménez, calling him 'the best infielder on the planet.'
